#: ../../B/bottom-feeder.rst:5
msgid "bottom feeder"
msgstr "bottom feeder"

#: ../../B/bottom-feeder.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../B/bottom-feeder.rst:10
msgid ""
"An Internet user that leeches off ISPs — the sort you can never provide good"
" enough services for, always complains about the price, no matter how low it"
" may be, and will bolt off to another service the moment there is even the "
"slimmest price difference. While most bottom feeders infest free or almost "
"free services such as AOL, MSN, and Hotmail, too many flock to whomever "
"happens to be the cheapest regional ISP at the time. Bottom feeders are "
"often the classic problem user, known for unleashing spam, flamage, and "
"other breaches of :ref:`netiquette`\\."
msgstr ""
"ISPに寄生するインターネットユーザー——どれだけ良いサービスを提供しても満足せず、どんなに安かろうと価格に文句を言い、ほんのわずかでも価格差があればたちまち別のサービスへ逃げ出す類の者。たいていのbottom"
" feederはAOL、MSN、Hotmailのような無料か無料に近いサービスにたかるが、その時々で最も安い地域ISPに群がる者も多すぎる。bottom"
" feederはしばしば古典的な問題ユーザーであり、スパムやflame、その他の\\ :ref:`netiquette`\\ "
"違反を解き放つことで知られる。"

#: ../../B/bottom-feeder.rst:15
msgid ""
"Syn. for :ref:`slopsucker`\\, derived from the fishermen's and naturalists' "
"term for finny creatures who subsist on the primordial ooze. (This sense is "
"older.)"
msgstr ""
"\\ :ref:`slopsucker`\\ の同義語。原初のぬかるみで生きる魚類を指す漁師や博物学者の用語に由来する。(こちらの語義のほうが古い。)"
